  "commentary": "With SPX at 6821 sitting below the GEX flip at 6848, dealers are in positive gamma territory and likely buying this dip to hedge their short positions, providing natural support. The massive +5.8B gamma wall at 6900 creates a strong ceiling where dealers will aggressively sell any rally attempts, while the regime suggests mean reversion back toward the 6848 flip level.\n\nKey levels: watch for dealer buying support around current levels with upside capped hard at 6900, and monitor the 6700 negative gamma floor as the backstop where dealer buying would accelerate if we break lower.\n\nBottom line: expect the market to grind back up toward 6850 but struggle to break much higher.",
